These rifles are built using the same quality and knowledge seen in our Saiga 12 models. Each rifle is stripped to a shell. All parts are media blazed to remove all traces of the cheap spray paint applied by the Russian's. We take the time to remove a portion of the barrel shroud and thread the barrel in the standard 1/14 LH Russian threads and add a flash suppressor. We also modified the mag release to accept ANY standard AK magazine INCLUDING DRUMS. Bullet Guide installed to assure feeding of ANY AND ALL ammo.

These rifles like all our firearms are refinished in Cerakote Firearms Coating. Cerakote it the best and most durable finish on the market. It is 100% solvent proof and rock hard. Another advantage is it has built in lubrication in the form of teflon in the coating matrix. This makes for an extremely smooth operating rifle.

title: For Sale:  Springfield Haemmerli International Match Rifle
postcontent: Offered is a Extraordinarily RARE US Military Springfield Haemmerli International Match Rifle in 30/06. SN 473. According to the "The Springfield 1903 Rifle" by Brophy (pg 128-129) the Ordnance Department purchased 10 of these rifles after the 1927 International Competitions fitting them with 31 inch heavy barrels (1 inch across the muzzle),Swiss Globe front sights,target scope blocks, Lyman 48 Receiver sights, palm rests, dbl set triggers, Scheuzen style check pieces, elaborate Trigger Guards and Butt Stocks. Others were offered for sale through the DCM and NRA at a cost of $231.46 from 1929 to 1932 for a total of about 40 rifles. "Few of these scarce rifles have survived in original condition" This rifle will letter through the SRS, as it has in the past. The condition of this is very fine plus with 96% to 98% strong blue on the barrel, 95% original blue with some freckles of light rust on the Receiver. The wood is sound with minor nicks and scratches and a hairline crack in the butt stock behind the butt plate attaching pin escutcheon, it retains most of its original fine hand rubbed oil finish. The mechanics are excellent with a bright and shiny bore. If one has any question please feel free to ask. This CR OK, IF paid with MO or Certified funds I usually ship within 24 hours with a MO, personal checks and Certified have to clear. Buyer to pay shipping, Weight of this rifle is 14 lbs and WILL HAVE to be shipped USPS REGISTERED MAIL to insure it adequately. Reasonable offers will be entertained. This is a rare and hard rifle to find,it could take years to find one let alone one as nice.--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 5/9/12 It has recently been brought to my attention that several of these Springfield Hammerillis (SN 434 and SN 456) have been sold at auction for substantially less than my offering price. After closely examining the auction catalogs multiple photos it is very clear that one has a large crack in the stock at the back of the Receiver, has a non configuration Springfield barrel and in general the condition of the stock, receiver & barrel and small parts in particular the Trigger assembly DO NOT tell the same story. It therefore appears that one of the two is REFINSIHED. The second ones pictures are a bit too vague to determine exactly what is going on with that rifle however again the barrel appears to be a replacement and the stock and metal parts condition seems to be at odds with each other. Also both rifle appear to have been shot either not at all or very little after they were blued. One MUST REMEMBER that Springfield Hammerillis rifles WERE SHOT both before and after they were sold through the DCM in the 1930's and to be in original condition need to show some commensurate wear. Again to quote Brophy, "Very few of these scarce rifles have survived in ORIGINAL condition."

title: For Sale/Trade:  Scam alert!!!!! ANTHONY VICKY...................SCAM ARTIST
postcontent: Here we go guys, another scam artist. Heres the M.O. They say they would like to pay with a certified check since they are disabled or unable to pick up personaly. So, you give an address , name, etc and a check arrives for alot more than the asking price. they tell you that the pick up person will come take the extra cash once you have cashed it and they will give you extra money for the inconvenience. YOU WILL BE LIABLE FOR THE OVERDRAFT WITH THE FAKE CASHIERS CHECK THAT WAS SENT!!!! This is an old scam, but I see the scammers have made it onto this site. We have seen this many times through our P.D. , so Just a heads up fellas............

postcontent:
NEW parkerizing tanks, lids, & checmicals for refinishing your parkerized finish on your military weapons, 1911's or whatever else you would like. 

I have for sale 2 new/never used stainless steel parkerizing tanks with lids and ½” drain valves. I bought these thinking I was going to learn how to parkerize guns but never got around to it so these have just been sitting collecting dust. Also included with this is 1 gallon of Zinc Phosphate Parkerizing Solution and 1 gallon of Post Treatment Solution, both new and unopened. Each gallon of chemical is concentrated and gets mixed with 4 gallons of water for 5 total gallons of each, which is the capacity of each tank. 

I paid right around $450 shipped to the door for the pair of tanks/lids plus around $125 shipped to the door for the chemicals. I have around $575 wrapped up in this but I will sell everything as a set for $400 cash or $450 trade value. Located in Dublin and you must be willing to meet in the Dublin area for the sale. Trades considered would possibly be 12 ga. shotguns, rifles, handguns in 9mm (no Hi-Point, Kel-Tec, or Jennings), ammo in 9mm (brass cased), .22LR (high velocity only), .223 (40-52 grain, brass), .308 (155-168 grain, brass). Not interested in bows, crossbows, or black powder.

Here is the description of the tanks from the manufacturer:

6"x6"x40", pure 304 Stainless Steel. Tank, cover, and Stainless Steel ball valve are included. 

We are proud to offer the very best Parkerizing Tanks in the industry. They are cut and formed out of pure 304 stainless steel. Handles are formed right into the ends. All edges of these tanks are hemmed, so there are no exposed sharp edges. Feel free to handle these tank with your bare hands! 

The tanks are TIG welded using supreme skill and elaborate tooling. The outside of the welds are treated and polished to reveal the beauty of the stainless steel and show the excellence of the weld. We maintain complete passivation inside the weld during manufacturing. Please look at the last picture taken of the inside of the weld, you will see that it remains brilliant and shiny. If you see a weld in stainless steel that is black or rust colored inside this means that proper provisions were not taken and rust and breakdown will start immediately when your liquid is applied.
